.","spans":[]}],"boxType":"downloadable","downloadFile":{"fileLink":"https://nutmegnewbrand.cdn.prismic.io/nutmegnewbrand/186f108d-5583-4859-9949-0a30e7015be7_27.01.2022+-+SRI+Whitepaper.pdf","fileName":"27.01.2022 - SRI Whitepaper.pdf"},"consent":[{"type":"paragraph","text":"","spans":[]}],"warning":null,"formName":"SRI-white-paper","image":{"src":"https://images.prismic.io/nutmegnewbrand/348316af-4274-42d8-82ba-434710d7c317_SRI-thumbnail-desktop.jpg?auto=compress,format","alt":null,"mobile":{"src":"https://images.prismic.io/nutmegnewbrand/91682c25-e564-41c5-9db7-bebcae52ad59_SRI-thumbnail-mobile.jpg?auto=compress,format","alt":null}},"hideOnPhone":false,"hideOnTablet":false},{"type":"spacing_section","size":"sm","color":"white"},{"type":"rich_text","text":[{"type":"image","url":"https://images.prismic.io/nutmegnewbrand/5a33f6e6-0ddc-41ce-9b76-e5799ebd1cbc_Waves.png?auto=compress,format","alt":null,"copyright":null,"dimensions":{"width":100,"height":50}}],"spacing":"default","alignment":"center","backrgoundColor":"white","noStack":false,"id":null},{"type":"track_record","heading":{"text":"Past performance and asset allocation","level":"1"},"text":[{"type":"paragraph","text":"Below you can see a detailed breakdown of our performance, as well as an indication of how our investments are allocated across global financial markets.","spans":[]}],"entries":[{"type":"track_record","model":{"documentID":"YURMnhAAACAA47a9"},"tabTitle":"Track record","title":{"text":"Track record","level":"1"},"description":[{"type":"paragraph","text":"Explore our track record for each of our 10 risk-based socially responsible portfolios.\n\nThis past performance is based on client data. Past performance is not a reliable indicator of future performance.","spans":[{"start":55,"end":86,"type":"strong"},{"start":89,"end":203,"type":"strong"}]}],"modalTriggerText":"Learn more about performance","modalText":[{"type":"paragraph","text":"Our returns","spans":[{"start":0,"end":11,"type":"strong"}]},{"type":"paragraph","text":"The returns shown here are regarded as simulated as they do not represent a single client account or an average of client returns. The data is calculated using actual Nutmeg trading data from client accounts, using actual trades carried out at market prices, and is based on an account size of £25,000. The returns are calculated after Nutmeg management fees, calculated as the weighted average rate paid by Nutmeg clients of 0.82% per year, VAT where applicable, prior to 01/02/2016, 0.72% between 01/02/2016 and 01/02/2017 and 0.64% thereafter. Returns also account for investment fund costs and the effect of market spread. Dividends have been included on an accrual basis. Source of price data: Bloomberg, Macrobond AB.","spans":[]},{"type":"paragraph","text":"Average competitor returns","spans":[{"start":0,"end":26,"type":"strong"}]},{"type":"paragraph","text":"This data is based on monthly results published by Asset Risk Consultants (ARC). ARC compute the average returns from discretionary investment managers based on risk profile, after fees. These include results from firms such as Barclays Wealth & Investment Management, Coutts & Co, JP Morgan Private Bank, UBS, Rathbones, Rothschild Wealth Management, and others. For example, the Sterling Balanced Asset Private Client Index (PCI) is a group of portfolios managed with equity risk aimed at between 40%-60% of volatility of global stock markets. For Nutmeg risk levels 3-4 the Sterling Cautious index (0-40% Equity Risk) is used, for 5-6 the Sterling Balanced Asset index (40%-60% Equity Risk), for 7-8 the Sterling Steady Growth index (60%-80% Equity Risk), and for 9-10 the Sterling Equity Risk Index (80%-120% Equity Risk). ARC do not provide data for portfolios equivalent to Nutmeg risk levels 1–2. Source data: Macrobond AB.","spans":[]}],"belowText":[{"type":"paragraph","text":"*The annualised figure is the return since inception expressed as a compound annual rate. For example, a portfolio with an annualised return of 6% corresponds to an actual return of 19.1% over three years (rather than 18% as you might expect) due to the effect of compounding. Please note, for the Nutmeg vs ARC comparison we are comparing Nutmeg SRI portfolio data vs ARC Non-SRI data.","spans":[{"start":264,"end":275,"type":"hyperlink","data":{"link_type":"Web","url":"https://www.nutmeg.com/nutmegonomics/the-extraordinary-power-of-compound-returns/","target":"_blank"}}]}],"link":{"cta":"primary","button":true,"title":"Sign up","href":"https://api.nutmeg.com/onboarding/start","trackInfo":[{"type":null,"event":null,"payload":[]}],"image":null,"isExternal":false},"riskWarning":"Capital at risk.","riskLevel":{"min":1,"max":10,"default":10},"investmentStyle":"sri"},{"type":"allocation","model":{"documentID":"YTtrkBAAACIAvI-z"},"tabTitle":"Asset allocation","title":{"text":"Allocation","level":"3"},"description":[{"type":"paragraph","text":"The allocation of assets within a chosen portfolio will vary depending on your chosen risk level and investment style. Your portfolio will typically hold a large majority in equities and investing the balance in bonds to help dampen the ups and downs of the portfolio.","spans":[]}],"modalTriggerText":null,"modalText":[],"belowText":[],"link":{"cta":"primary","button":true,"title":"Sign up","href":"https://api.nutmeg.com/onboarding/start","trackInfo":[{"type":null,"event":null,"payload":[]}],"image":null,"isExternal":false},"riskWarning":"Capital at risk","riskLevel":{"min":1,"max":10,"default":10}},{"type":"allocation","model":{"documentID":"YTtrkBAAACIAvJAj"},"tabTitle":"Countries allocation","title":{"text":"Allocation","level":"3"},"description":[{"type":"paragraph","text":"The allocation of countries within a chosen portfolio will vary depending on your chosen risk level and investment style. Broadly, your portfolio will be split between UK and non-UK markets.","spans":[]}],"modalTriggerText":null,"modalText":[],"belowText":[],"link":{"cta":"prima